00099                 void print(std::ostream &o, RenameMap *rmap=NULL) const {
00100                     FormatRestorer restorer(o); // restore format flags when we leave this scope
00101                     uint64_t sign_bit = (uint64_t)1 << (nBits-1); /* e.g., 80000000 */
00102                     uint64_t val_mask = sign_bit - 1;             /* e.g., 7fffffff */
00103                     /*magnitude of negative value*/
00104                     uint64_t negative = nBits>1 && (offset & sign_bit) ? (~offset & val_mask) + 1 : 0;
00105 
00106                     if (name!=0) {
00107                         /* This is a named value rather than a constant. */
00108                         uint64_t renamed = name;
00109                         if (rmap) {
00110                             RenameMap::iterator found = rmap->find(name);
00111                             if (found==rmap->end()) {
00112                                 renamed = rmap->size()+1;
00113                                 rmap->insert(std::make_pair(name, renamed));
00114                             } else {
00115                                 renamed = found->second;
00116                             }
00117                         }
00118                         const char *sign = negate ? "-" : "";
00119                         o <<sign <<"v" <<std::dec <<renamed;
00120                         if (negative) {
00121                             o <<"-0x" <<std::hex <<negative;
00122                         } else if (offset) {
00123                             o <<"+0x" <<std::hex <<offset;
00124                         }
00125                     } else {
00126                         /* This is a constant */
00127                         ROSE_ASSERT(!negate);
00128                         o  <<"0x" <<std::hex <<offset;
00129                         if (negative)
00130                             o <<" (-0x" <<std::hex <<negative <<")";
00131                     }
00132                 }

00391                 template <size_t Len> ValueType<Len> mem_read(State<ValueType> &state, const ValueType<32> &addr) const {
00392                     MemoryCell<ValueType> new_cell(addr, ValueType<32>(), Len/8);
00393                     bool aliased = false; /*is new_cell aliased by any existing writes?*/
00394 
00395                     for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::iterator mi=state.memory.begin(); mi!=state.memory.end(); ++mi) {
00396                         if (new_cell.must_alias(*mi)) {
00397                             if (mi->is_clobbered()) {
00398                                 mi->set_clobbered(false);
00399                                 mi->set_data(new_cell.get_data());
00400                                 return new_cell.get_data();
00401                             } else {
00402                                 return mi->get_data();
00403                             }
00404                         } else if (new_cell.may_alias(*mi) && mi->is_written()) {
00405                             aliased = true;
00406                         }
00407                     }
00408 
00409                     if (!aliased && &state!=&orig_state) {
00410                         /* We didn't find the memory cell in the specified state and it's not aliased to any writes in that
00411                          * state. Therefore use the value from the initial memory state (creating it if necessary). */
00412                         for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::iterator mi=orig_state.memory.begin();
00413                              mi!=orig_state.memory.end();
00414                              ++mi) {
00415                             if (new_cell.must_alias(*mi)) {
00416                                 ROSE_ASSERT(!(*mi).is_clobbered());
00417                                 ROSE_ASSERT(!(*mi).is_written());
00418                                 state.memory.push_back(*mi);
00419                                 return (*mi).get_data();
00420                             }
00421                         }
00422 
00423                         /* Not found in initial state. But if we have a known address and a valid memory map then initialize
00424                          * the original state with data from the memory map. */      
00425                         if (map && addr.is_known()) {
00426                             uint8_t buf[sizeof(uint64_t)];
00427                             ROSE_ASSERT(Len/8 < sizeof buf);
00428                             size_t nread = map->read(buf, addr.known_value(), Len/8);
00429                             if (nread==Len/8) {
00430                                 uint64_t n = 0;
00431                                 for (size_t i=0; i<Len/8; i++)
00432                                     n |= buf[i] << (8*i);
00433                                 new_cell.set_data(number<32>(n));
00434                             }
00435                         }
00436 
00437                         orig_state.memory.push_back(new_cell);
00438                     }
00439 
00440                     /* Create the cell in the current state. */
00441                     state.memory.push_back(new_cell);
00442                     return new_cell.get_data();
00443                 }

00452                 MemRefType memory_reference_type(const State<ValueType> &state, const ValueType<32> &addr) const {
00453                     if (addr.name) {

00455                         if (addr.name==state.registers.gpr[x86_gpr_bp].name) return MRT_FRAME_PTR;
00456                         return MRT_OTHER_PTR;
00457                     }
00458                     if (addr==state.registers.gpr[x86_gpr_sp]) return MRT_STACK_PTR;
00459                     if (addr==state.registers.gpr[x86_gpr_bp]) return MRT_FRAME_PTR;
00460                     return MRT_OTHER_PTR;

00466                 template <size_t Len> void mem_write(State<ValueType> &state, const ValueType<32> &addr,
00467                                                      const ValueType<Len> &data) {
00468                     ROSE_ASSERT(&state!=&orig_state);
00469                     MemoryCell<ValueType> new_cell(addr, data, Len/8);
00470                     new_cell.set_written();
00471                     bool saved = false; /* has new_cell been saved into memory? */
00472 
00473                     /* Is new memory reference through the stack pointer or frame pointer? */
00474                     MemRefType new_mrt = memory_reference_type(state, addr);
00475 
00476                     /* Overwrite and/or clobber existing memory locations. */
00477                     for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::iterator mi=state.memory.begin(); mi!=state.memory.end(); ++mi) {
00478                         if (new_cell.must_alias(*mi)) {
00479                             *mi = new_cell;
00480                             saved = true;
00481                         } else if (p_discard_popped_memory && new_mrt!=memory_reference_type(state, (*mi).get_address())) {
00482                             /* Assume that memory referenced through the stack pointer does not alias that which is referenced
00483                              * through the frame pointer, and neither of them alias memory that is referenced other ways. */
00484                         } else if (new_cell.may_alias(*mi)) {
00485                             (*mi).set_clobbered();
00486                         } else {
00487                             /* memory cell *mi is not aliased to cell being written */
00488                         }
00489                     }
00490                     if (!saved)
00491                         state.memory.push_back(new_cell);
00492                 }

00615                 template <size_t Len>
00616                 ValueType<Len> add(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<Len> &b) const {
00617                     if (a.name==b.name && (!a.name || a.negate!=b.negate)) {
00618                         /* [V1+x] + [-V1+y] = [x+y]  or
00619                          * [x] + [y] = [x+y] */
00620                         return ValueType<Len>(a.offset + b.offset);
00621                     } else if (!a.name || !b.name) {
00622                         /* [V1+x] + [y] = [V1+x+y]   or
00623                          * [x] + [V2+y] = [V2+x+y]   or
00624                          * [-V1+x] + [y] = [-V1+x+y] or
00625                          * [x] + [-V2+y] = [-V2+x+y] */
00626                         return ValueType<Len>(a.name+b.name, a.offset+b.offset, a.negate || b.negate);
00627                     } else {
00628                         return ValueType<Len>();
00629                     }
00630                 }

00633                 template <size_t Len>
00634                 ValueType<Len> addWithCarries(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<Len> &b, const ValueType<1> &c,
00635                                               ValueType<Len> &carry_out) const {
00636                     int n_unknown = (a.name?1:0) + (b.name?1:0) + (c.name?1:0);
00637                     if (n_unknown <= 1) {
00638                         /* At most, one of the operands is an unknown value. See add() for more details. */
00639                         uint64_t sum = a.offset + b.offset + c.offset;
00640                         carry_out = 0==n_unknown ? ValueType<Len>((a.offset ^ b.offset ^ sum)>>1) : ValueType<Len>();
00641                         return ValueType<Len>(a.name+b.name+c.name, sum, a.negate||b.negate||c.negate);
00642                     } else if (a.name==b.name && !c.name && a.negate!=b.negate) {
00643                         /* A and B are known or have bases that cancel out, and C is known */
00644                         uint64_t sum = a.offset + b.offset + c.offset;
00645                         carry_out = ValueType<Len>((a.offset ^ b.offset ^ sum)>>1);
00646                         return ValueType<Len>(sum);
00647                     } else {
00648                         carry_out = ValueType<Len>();
00649                         return ValueType<Len>();
00650                     }
00651                 }

00713                 template <size_t Len>
00714                 ValueType<Len> negate(const ValueType<Len> &a) const {
00715                     if (a.name) return ValueType<Len>(a.name, -a.offset, !a.negate);
00716                     return ValueType<Len>(-a.offset);
00717                 }
00718 
00720                 template <size_t Len>
00721                 ValueType<Len> or_(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<Len> &b) const {
00722                     if (a==b) return a;
00723                     if (!a.name && !b.name) return ValueType<Len>(a.offset | b.offset);
00724                     if (!a.name && a.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, Len>::value) return a;
00725                     if (!b.name && b.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, Len>::value) return b;
00726                     return ValueType<Len>();
00727                 }

00730                 template <size_t Len, size_t SALen>
00731                 ValueType<Len> rotateLeft(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<SALen> &sa) const {
00732                     if (!a.name && !sa.name) return ValueType<Len>(IntegerOps::rotateLeft<Len>(a.offset, sa.offset));
00733                     if (!sa.name && 0==sa.offset % Len) return a;
00734                     return ValueType<Len>();
00735                 }

00738                 template <size_t Len, size_t SALen>
00739                 ValueType<Len> rotateRight(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<SALen> &sa) const {
00740                     if (!a.name && !sa.name) return ValueType<Len>(IntegerOps::rotateRight<Len>(a.offset, sa.offset));
00741                     if (!sa.name && 0==sa.offset % Len) return a;
00742                     return ValueType<Len>();
00743                 }

00746                 template <size_t Len, size_t SALen>
00747                 ValueType<Len> shiftLeft(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<SALen> &sa) const {
00748                     if (!a.name && !sa.name) return ValueType<Len>(IntegerOps::shiftLeft<Len>(a.offset, sa.offset));
00749                     if (!sa.name) {
00750                         if (0==sa.offset) return a;
00751                         if (sa.offset>=Len) return ValueType<Len>(0);
00752                     }
00753                     return ValueType<Len>();
00754                 }

00759                     if (!a.name && !sa.name) return ValueType<Len>(IntegerOps::shiftRightLogical<Len>(a.offset, sa.offset));
00760                     if (!sa.name) {
00761                         if (0==sa.offset) return a;
00762                         if (sa.offset>=Len) return ValueType<Len>(0);
00763                     }
00764                     return ValueType<Len>();

00771                     if (!sa.name && 0==sa.offset) return a;

00776                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00777                 ValueType<Len1> signedDivide(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00778                     if (!b.name) {
00779                         if (0==b.offset) throw Exception("division by zero");
00780                         if (!a.name)
00781                             return ValueType<Len1>(IntegerOps::signExtend<Len1, 64>(a.offset) /
00782                                                    IntegerOps::signExtend<Len2, 64>(b.offset));
00783                         if (1==b.offset) return a;
00784                         if (b.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t,Len2>::value) return negate(a);
00785                         /*FIXME: also possible to return zero if B is large enough. [RPM 2010-05-18]*/
00786                     }
00787                     return ValueType<Len1>();
00788                 }

00791                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00792                 ValueType<Len2> signedModulo(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00793                     if (a.name || b.name) return ValueType<Len2>();
00794                     if (0==b.offset) throw Exception("division by zero");
00795                     return ValueType<Len2>(IntegerOps::signExtend<Len1, 64>(a.offset) %
00796                                            IntegerOps::signExtend<Len2, 64>(b.offset));
00797                     /* FIXME: More folding possibilities... if 'b' is a power of two then we can return 'a' with the bitsize of
00798                      * 'b'. */
00799                 }

00802                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00803                 ValueType<Len1+Len2> signedMultiply(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00804                     if (!a.name && !b.name)
00805                         return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(IntegerOps::signExtend<Len1, 64>(a.offset) *
00806                                                     IntegerOps::signExtend<Len2, 64>(b.offset));
00807                     if (!b.name) {
00808                         if (0==b.offset) return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(0);
00809                         if (1==b.offset) return signExtend<Len1, Len1+Len2>(a);
00810                         if (b.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t,Len2>::value) return signExtend<Len1, Len1+Len2>(negate(a));
00811                     }
00812                     if (!a.name) {
00813                         if (0==a.offset) return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(0);
00814                         if (1==a.offset) return signExtend<Len2, Len1+Len2>(b);
00815                         if (a.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t,Len1>::value) return signExtend<Len2, Len1+Len2>(negate(b));
00816                     }
00817                     return ValueType<Len1+Len2>();
00818                 }

00821                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00822                 ValueType<Len1> unsignedDivide(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00823                     if (!b.name) {
00824                         if (0==b.offset) throw Exception("division by zero");
00825                         if (!a.name) return ValueType<Len1>(a.offset / b.offset);
00826                         if (1==b.offset) return a;
00827                         /*FIXME: also possible to return zero if B is large enough. [RPM 2010-05-18]*/
00828                     }
00829                     return ValueType<Len1>();
00830                 }
00831 
00833                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00834                 ValueType<Len2> unsignedModulo(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00835                     if (!b.name) {
00836                         if (0==b.offset) throw Exception("division by zero");
00837                         if (!a.name) return ValueType<Len2>(a.offset % b.offset);
00838                         /* FIXME: More folding possibilities... if 'b' is a power of two then we can return 'a' with the
00839                          * bitsize of 'b'. */
00840                     }
00841                     if (unsignedExtend<Len1,64>(a)==unsignedExtend<Len2,64>(b)) return b;
00842                     return ValueType<Len2>();
00843                 }
00844 
00846                 template <size_t Len1, size_t Len2>
00847                 ValueType<Len1+Len2> unsignedMultiply(const ValueType<Len1> &a, const ValueType<Len2> &b) const {
00848                     if (!a.name && !b.name)
00849                         return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(a.offset * b.offset);
00850                     if (!b.name) {
00851                         if (0==b.offset) return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(0);
00852                         if (1==b.offset) return unsignedExtend<Len1, Len1+Len2>(a);
00853                     }
00854                     if (!a.name) {
00855                         if (0==a.offset) return ValueType<Len1+Len2>(0);
00856                         if (1==a.offset) return unsignedExtend<Len2, Len1+Len2>(b);
00857                     }
00858                     return ValueType<Len1+Len2>();
00859                 }
00860 
00862                 template <size_t Len>
00863                 ValueType<Len> xor_(const ValueType<Len> &a, const ValueType<Len> &b) const {
00864                     if (!a.name && !b.name)
00865                         return ValueType<Len>(a.offset ^ b.offset);
00866                     if (a==b)
00867                         return ValueType<Len>(0);
00868                     if (!b.name) {
00869                         if (0==b.offset) return a;
00870                         if (b.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, Len>::value) return invert(a);
00871                     }
00872                     if (!a.name) {
00873                         if (0==a.offset) return b;
00874                         if (a.offset==IntegerOps::GenMask<uint64_t, Len>::value) return invert(b);
00875                     }
00876                     return ValueType<Len>();
00877                 }
00878             };

00885             template<size_t Len> ValueType<Len>
00886             ValueType<Len>::rename(RenameMap *rmap) const
00887             {
00888                 ValueType<Len> retval = *this;
00889                 if (rmap && name>0) {
00890                     RenameMap::iterator found = rmap->find(name);
00891                     if (found==rmap->end()) {
00892                         retval.name = rmap->size()+1;
00893                         rmap->insert(std::make_pair(name, retval.name));
00894                     } else {
00895                         retval.name = found->second;
00896                     }
00897                 }
00898                 return retval;
00899             }

00907             template<template <size_t> class ValueType>
00908             bool
00909             MemoryCell<ValueType>::may_alias(const MemoryCell &other) const {
00910                 const ValueType<32> &addr1 = this->address;
00911                 const ValueType<32> &addr2 = other.address;
00912                 if (addr1.name != addr2.name) return true;
00913 
00914                 /* Same unknown values but inverses (any offset). */
00915                 if (addr1.name && addr1.negate!=addr2.negate) return true;
00916 
00917                 /* If they have the same base values (or are both constant) then check the offsets. The 32-bit casts are
00918                  * purportedly necessary to wrap propertly, but I'm not sure this will work for addresses (LatticeElements)
00919                  * that have a length other than 32 bits. [FIXME RPM 2009-02-03]. */
00920                 uint32_t offsetDiff = (uint32_t)(addr1.offset - addr2.offset);
00921                 if (offsetDiff < this->nbytes || offsetDiff > (uint32_t)(-other.nbytes))
00922                     return true;
00923                 return false;
00924             }
00925 
00926             template<template<size_t> class ValueType>
00927             bool
00928             MemoryCell<ValueType>::must_alias(const MemoryCell<ValueType> &other) const {
00929                 return this->address == other.address;
00930             }

00937             void
00938             State<ValueType>::print_diff_registers(std::ostream &o, const State &other, RenameMap *rmap/*=NULL*/) const
00939             {
00940 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
00941                 // DQ (5/22/2010): This code does not compile using ROSE, it needs to be investigated to be reduced to an bug
00942                 // report.
00943

00945 
00946                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_gprs; ++i) {
00947                     if (this->registers.gpr[i]!=other.registers.gpr[i]) {

00949                           <<this->registers.gpr[i].rename(rmap) <<" -> " <<other.registers.gpr[i].rename(rmap) <<"\n";
00950                     }
00951                 }
00952                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_segregs; ++i) {
00953                     if (this->registers.segreg[i]!=other.registers.segreg[i]) {
00954                         o <<prefix <<segregToString((X86SegmentRegister)i) <<": "
00955                           <<this->registers.segreg[i].rename(rmap) <<" -> " <<other.registers.segreg[i].rename(rmap) <<"\n";
00956                     }
00957                 }
00958                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_flags; ++i) {
00959                     if (this->registers.flag[i]!=other.registers.flag[i]) {
00960                         o <<prefix <<flagToString((X86Flag)i) <<": "
00961                           <<this->registers.flag[i].rename(rmap) <<" -> " <<other.registers.flag[i].rename(rmap) <<"\n";
00962                     }
00963                 }
00964                 if (this->registers.ip!=other.registers.ip) {
00965                     o <<prefix <<"ip: " <<this->registers.ip.rename(rmap) <<" -> " <<other.registers.ip.rename(rmap) <<"\n";
00966                 }

00970             template<template<size_t> class ValueType>
00971             bool
00972             State<ValueType>::equal_registers(const State &other) const
00973             {
00974 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
00975                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_gprs; ++i)
00976                     if (this->registers.gpr[i]!=other.registers.gpr[i]) return false;
00977                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_segregs; ++i)
00978                     if (this->registers.segreg[i]!=other.registers.segreg[i]) return false;
00979                 for (size_t i=0; i<this->registers.n_flags; ++i)
00980                     if (this->registers.flag[i]!=other.registers.flag[i]) return false;
00981                 if (this->registers.ip!=other.registers.ip) return false;
00982 #endif
00983                 return true;
00984             }

00986             template<template<size_t> class ValueType>
00987             void
00988             State<ValueType>::discard_popped_memory()
00989             {
00990                 Memory new_mem;
00991                 const ValueType<32> &sp = this->registers.gpr[x86_gpr_sp];
00992                 for (typename Memory::const_iterator mi=this->memory.begin(); mi!=this->memory.end(); ++mi) {
00993                     const ValueType<32> &addr = mi->get_address();
00994                     if (addr.name!=sp.name || addr.negate!=sp.negate || (int32_t)addr.offset>=(int32_t)sp.offset)
00995                         new_mem.push_back(*mi);
00996                 }
00997                 this->memory = new_mem;
00998             }

01004             /* Returns memory that needs to be compared by equal_states() */
01005             template<
01006                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01007                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01008             typename State<ValueType>::Memory
01009             Policy<State, ValueType>::memory_for_equality(const State<ValueType> &state) const
01010             {
01011                 State<ValueType> tmp_state = state;
01012                 typename State<ValueType>::Memory retval;
01013 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
01014                 for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::const_iterator mi=state.memory.begin(); mi!=state.memory.end(); ++mi) {
01015                     if (mi->is_written() && mi->get_data()!=mem_read<32>(orig_state, mi->get_address()))
01016                         retval.push_back(*mi);
01017                 }
01018 #endif
01019                 return retval;
01020             }

01022             template<
01023                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01024                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01025             bool
01026             Policy<State, ValueType>::equal_states(const State<ValueType> &s1, const State<ValueType> &s2) const
01027             {
01028 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
01029                 if (!s1.equal_registers(s2))
01030                     return false;
01031                 typename State<ValueType>::Memory m1 = memory_for_equality(s1);
01032                 typename State<ValueType>::Memory m2 = memory_for_equality(s2);
01033                 std::vector<typename State<ValueType>::Memory::value_type> v1(m1.begin(), m1.end());
01034                 std::vector<typename State<ValueType>::Memory::value_type> v2(m1.begin(), m1.end());
01035                 if (v1.size()!=v2.size())
01036                     return false;
01037                 std::sort(v1.begin(), v1.end());
01038                 std::sort(v2.begin(), v2.end());
01039                 for (size_t i=0; i<v1.size(); ++i) {
01040                     if (v1[i].get_nbytes() != v2[i].get_nbytes() ||
01041                         v1[i].get_address()!= v2[i].get_address() ||
01042                         v1[i].get_data()   != v2[i].get_data())
01043                         return false;
01044                 }
01045 #endif
01046                 return true;
01047             }

01058             template<
01059                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01060                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01061             void
01062             Policy<State, ValueType>::print_diff(std::ostream &o, const State<ValueType> &s1,
01063                                                  const State<ValueType> &s2, RenameMap *rmap/*=NULL*/) const
01064             {
01065 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
01066                 s1.print_diff_registers(o, s2, rmap);
01067 
01068                 /* Get all addresses that have been written and are not currently clobbered. */
01069                 std::set<ValueType<32> > addresses;
01070                 for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::const_iterator mi=s1.memory.begin(); mi!=s1.memory.end(); ++mi) {
01071                     if (!mi->is_clobbered() && mi->is_written())
01072                         addresses.insert(mi->get_address());
01073                 }
01074                 for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::const_iterator mi=s2.memory.begin(); mi!=s2.memory.end(); ++mi) {
01075                     if (!mi->is_clobbered() && mi->is_written())
01076                         addresses.insert(mi->get_address());
01077                 }
01078 
01079                 State<ValueType> tmp_s1 = s1;
01080                 State<ValueType> tmp_s2 = s2;
01081                 size_t nmemdiff = 0;
01082                 for (typename std::set<ValueType<32> >::const_iterator ai=addresses.begin(); ai!=addresses.end(); ++ai) {
01083                     ValueType<32> v1 = mem_read<32>(tmp_s1, *ai);
01084                     ValueType<32> v2 = mem_read<32>(tmp_s2, *ai);
01085                     if (v1 != v2) {
01086                         if (0==nmemdiff++) o <<"    memory:\n";
01087                         o <<"      " <<(*ai).rename(rmap) <<": " <<v1.rename(rmap) <<" -> " <<v2.rename(rmap) <<"\n";
01088                     }
01089                 }
01090 #endif
01091             }

01093             template<
01094                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01095                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01096             bool
01097             Policy<State, ValueType>::on_stack(const ValueType<32> &value) const
01098             {
01099 #ifndef CXX_IS_ROSE_ANALYSIS
01100                 const ValueType<32> sp_inverted = invert(cur_state.registers.gpr[x86_gpr_sp]);
01101                 for (typename State<ValueType>::Memory::const_iterator mi=cur_state.memory.begin();
01102                      mi!=cur_state.memory.end();
01103                      ++mi) {
01104                     if (mi->get_nbytes()!=4 || !(mi->get_data()==value)) continue;
01105                     const ValueType<32> &addr = mi->get_address();
01106 
01107                     /* Is addr >= sp? */
01108                     ValueType<32> carries = 0;
01109                     ValueType<32> diff = addWithCarries(addr, sp_inverted, true_(), carries/*out*/);
01110                     ValueType<1> sf = extract<31,32>(diff);
01111                     ValueType<1> of = xor_(extract<31,32>(carries), extract<30,31>(carries));
01112                     if (sf==of) return true;
01113                 }
01114 #endif
01115                 return false;
01116             }

01118             template<
01119                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01120                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01121             bool
01122             Policy<State, ValueType>::SHA1(unsigned char digest[20]) const
01123             {
01124 #ifdef ROSE_HAVE_GCRYPT_H
01125                 /* libgcrypt requires gcry_check_version() to be called "before any other function in the library", but doesn't
01126                  * include an API function for determining if this has already been performed. It also doesn't indicate what
01127                  * happens when it's called more than once, or how expensive the call is.  Therefore, instead of calling it
01128                  * every time through this function, we'll just call it the first time. */
01129                 static bool initialized = false;
01130                 if (!initialized) {
01131                     gcry_check_version(NULL);
01132                     initialized = true;
01133                 }
01134 
01135                 std::stringstream s;
01136                 RenameMap rmap;
01137                 print_diff(s, &rmap);
01138                 ROSE_ASSERT(gcry_md_get_algo_dlen(GCRY_MD_SHA1)==20);
01139                 gcry_md_hash_buffer(GCRY_MD_SHA1, digest, s.str().c_str(), s.str().size());
01140                 return true;
01141 #else
01142                 memset(digest, 0, 20);
01143                 return false;
01144 #endif
01145             }

01147             template<
01148                 template <template <size_t> class ValueType> class State,
01149                 template<size_t> class ValueType>
01150             std::string
01151             Policy<State, ValueType>::SHA1() const
01152             {
01153                 std::string digest_str;
01154                 unsigned char digest[20];
01155                 if (SHA1(digest)) {
01156                     for (size_t i=sizeof digest; i>0; --i) {
01157                         digest_str += "0123456789abcdef"[(digest[i-1] >> 4) & 0xf];
01158                         digest_str += "0123456789abcdef"[digest[i-1] & 0xf];
01159                     }
01160                 }
01161                 return digest_str;
01162             }
